A Transworld Airlines Inc official saidthe airline has no comment on USAir Group Inc's planned buyoutof Piedmont Aviation Inc.    TWA, however, has pursued its application with theDepartment of Transportation for a takeover of USAir, accordingto Mark Buckstein, TWA general counsel and vice president. TWAfiled a revised application today, following the DOT'srejection Friday of an incomplete application filed last week.    Earlier USAir said it agreed to buy Piedmont for 69 dlrscash per share.&#3;